cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper involves the application of graph neural networks (GNN) to improve signal detection in the IceCube neutrino observatory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as GNNs are a popular topic in this field. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) to improve signal classification. Additionally, the paper involves the use of computational engineering (cs.CE) to model the IceCube detector array as a graph. Finally, the paper involves the use of computational research (cs.CR) to develop a new method for signal classification in the IceCube observatory.
